ed modification of isolated $\\rm Fe_{2-z}Se_2$ ($z$, vacant sites)\nplanes, resembling the host layers, identify that Fe-site deficiency occurs at\nlow energy cost, giving rise to stretched Fe-sheets, in accord with\nexperiments. The robust high-$T_c$ in $\\rm Li_x(C_5H_5N)_yFe_{2-z}Se_2$, arises\nfrom the interplay of electron donating spacers and the iron-selenide layers\ntolerance to defect chemistry, a tool to favorably tune its Fermi surface\nproperties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 19 Mar 2023 16:57:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-21"}
{"id":"2303.10717","submitter":"Mihalis Mourgoglou","authors":"Mihalis Mourgoglou and Thanasis Zacharopoulos","title":"Varopoulos' extensions of boundary functions in $L^p$ and BMO in domains\n  with Ahlfors-regular boundaries","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP math.CA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $\\Omega \\subset \\mathbb{R}^{n+1}$, $n \\geq 1$, be an open set with\n$s$-Ahlfors regular boundary $\\partial \\Omega$, for some $s \\in(0,n]$, such\nthat either $s=n$ and $\\Omega$ is a corkscrew domain with the pointwise John\ncondition, or $s<n$ and $\\Omega= \\mathbb{R}^{n+1} \\setminus E$, for some\n$s$-Ahlfors regular set $E \\subset \\mathbb{R}^{n+1}$. In this paper we\nconstruct Varopoulos' type extensions of $L^p$ and $BMO$ boundary functions. In\nparticular, we show that a) if $f \\in L^p(\\partial \\Omega)$, $1 <p \\leq\n\\infty$, there exists $F\\in C^\\infty(\\Omega)$ such that the Carleson functional\nof $dist(x,\\Omega^c)^{s-n}\\nabla F(x)$ and the non-tangential maximal function\nof $F$ are in $L^p(\\partial \\Omega)$ with norms controlled by the $L^p$-norm of\n$f$, and $F \\to f$ in some non-tangential sense $\\mathcal{H}^s|_{\\partial\n\\Omega}$-almost everywhere; b) if $\\tilde f \\in BMO(\\partial \\Omega)$, there\nexists $\\tilde F\\in C^\\infty(\\Omega)$ such that $\\sup_{x\\in \\Omega} dist(x,\n\\Omega^c)|\\nabla \\tilde F(x)| \\leq C\\|\\tilde f\\|_{BMO(\\partial \\Omega)} $, the\nCarleson functional of $dist(x,\\Omega^c)^{s-n}\\nabla F(x)$ is in\n$L^\\infty(\\partial \\Omega)$ with norm controlled by the $BMO$-norm of $\\tilde\nf$, and $\\tilde F \\to \\tilde f$ in some non-tangential sense $\\mathcal\nH^s|_{\\partial \\Omega}$-almost everywhere. If, in addition, the boundary\nfunctions are Lipschitz with compact support, then both $F$ and $\\tilde F$ can\nbe modified so that they are also Lipschitz on $\\overline \\Omega$ and converge\nto the boundary data continuously. In the latter case, the pointwise John\ncondition when $s=n$ is only needed for the $BMO$ extension.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 19 Mar 2023 16:59:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-21"}
