posite ELGs. We\nfind that a Saunders function is the most appropriate to describe all the\nemission-line LFs. They are dominated by star-forming regions, except for the\nbright end of the [OIII] and [NII] LFs (i.e. L[NII]>10$^{42}$ erg/s,\nL[OIII]>10$^{43}$ erg/s), where the contribution of Seyfert galaxies is not\nnegligible. Besides the star-forming population, composite galaxies and LINERs\nare the ones that contribute the most to the ELG numbers at L<10$^{41}$ erg/s.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Mar 2023 11:34:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-21"}
