2+101. Additional contributions may come from leptonic\nprocesses in the shell of the supernova remnant, together with contributions\nfrom PSR J1913$+$1011 and its pulsar wind nebula and/or from the star-forming\nregion. A confident determination of the distance to the putative remnant is\nnecessary to determine whether these sources are associated or just appear\nsuperimposed in the line of sight.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Mar 2023 13:55:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-26"}
